# SYNAPSE — Project Rules for AI Agent

## Project
Synapse is a self-hosted enterprise AI assistant with RAG pipeline.
Full specification: docs/prompts/SYNAPSE_MASTER_PROMPT.md
ALWAYS read the relevant section of that file before implementing anything.

## Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.12+), async everywhere
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript strict mode
- Vector DB: Qdrant (HNSW, RBAC payload filtering)
- Graph DB: Neo4j 5 (Cypher)
- Relational DB: PostgreSQL 16 (via SQLAlchemy + Alembic)
- LLM: Ollama (local, Llama 3 8B)
- Embeddings: Sentence-Transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 768 dim)
- Task Queue: Celery + Redis
- Containers: Docker Compose

## Backend Rules (MUST follow)
- Every function has type hints. No `Any`.
- Every endpoint has Pydantic request + response schema.
- Every DB query is parameterized. NEVER f-strings for SQL.
- NEVER use print(). Use structlog for ALL logging.
- NEVER hardcode secrets. Use Pydantic Settings + env vars.
- ALL external calls have timeouts + retries (tenacity).
- Follow PEP-8. Max line length 100.
- Use FastAPI Depends() for dependency injection.
- ALL list endpoints support pagination.
- Use Alembic for ALL schema changes.

## Frontend Rules (MUST follow)
- TypeScript strict mode. NO `any` type. Ever.
- ALL components handle 3 states: loading, error, success.
- NEVER inline styles. Use Tailwind + CSS variables.
- Dark mode is DEFAULT. Light mode secondary.
- Self-host ALL fonts. No external CDNs.
- Use framer-motion for animations.
- Semantic HTML (main, nav, article). No div soup.

## UI Design Rules (CRITICAL — not negotiable)
- Font: General Sans (display) + JetBrains Mono (code)
- DO NOT use: Inter, Roboto, Arial, system fonts
- DO NOT use: purple/blue gradients, rounded cards with shadows everywhere
- DO NOT use: generic AI-generated aesthetics
- Color: Dark charcoal (#0A0A0F) + electric cyan accent (#00E5CC)
- Cards: 1px border, 12px radius, NO drop shadow in dark mode
- Buttons: 6px radius, bold text, glow hover on primary
- Inputs: bottom-border style, accent color on focus

## Error Handling
- Custom exception hierarchy (SynapseError base class)
- Global exception handler catches all + returns structured JSON
- NEVER expose raw exceptions to client
- Request ID on every response for tracing

